thread.title: Pa. football: St. Joseph's Prep knocks off New Jersey power

title: Pa. football: St. Joseph's Prep knocks off New Jersey power
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports St. Joseph Regional is ranked No. 1 in New Jersey by NJ.com and No. 24 nationally by Maxpreps.com.
Earlier in the season, St. Joseph Regional picked up a 17-7 win over Don Bosco Prep. Bosco beat St. Joseph's Prep, 55-21, on Sept. 12. 
In other nonleague play: 
Shayne Smith threw for 199 yards and a pair of touchdowns in Del-Val Charter's 37-29 victory over West York at Northwest Super Site. Jahmir Nuble rushed for three touchdowns. 
Nate Jones had 13 carries for 255 yards and four touchdowns in Avon Grove's 41-0 rout of visiting Octorara. Shane McLaughlin completed 8 of 9 passes for 145 yards and a touchdown. 
Blake Hildebrandt took a Nick Garritano pass 3 yards for a touchdown in New Hope-Solebury's 9-0 shutout at Academy of New Church. 
Catholic AAA. Matt Romano completed 12 of 20 passes for 242 yards and a pair of touchdowns in Archbishop Ryan's 35-12 win over Bonner-Prendergast at Upper Darby. Jason Wagher (42 yards) and Drew Obuchowicz (28 yards) each returned an interception for a score. Jaye McNeil had 22 carries for 93 yards and a third-quarter touchdown. 
Public AA. Quadir Strothers ran for three touchdowns, including a 75-yard run to start the scoring, to lead Prep Charter over Strawberry Mansion, 40-0, at the South Philly Super Site. The senior finished with 177 rushing yards on four carries. 
Suburban One Continental. Alex Gibson rushed for two touchdowns to carry No. 22 Central Bucks East over visiting William Tennent, 28-3. Matt Szczypiorski connected with Sammy Killough on a touchdown pass. Ethan Silverman ran for a touchdown to round out the scoring. 
Bicentennial. Michael Hollinger ran for two touchdowns in host Calvary Christian's 42- 16 rout of Morrisville. 
Eli Moore and Daryl Mehn each rushed for a touchdown in Bristol's 26-0 shutout of visiting Jenkintown. 
Del-Val. Teddy Wright had a 26-yard touchdown run and two interceptions in No. 20 Academy Park's 49-7 win at Penn Wood. 
Central. Jack Donaghy threw three touchdowns, including a pair to Chris Trainor, in host Haverford High's 29-21 victory over Garnet Valley. Derrick West rushed for two touchdowns for the visitors.
